
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Researcher {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -researchGroupId: int
}

class ResearchGroup {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -departmentId: int
}

class Department {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class Project {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

class WorkPackage {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -projectId: int
  -researchGroupId: int
}

class Assignment {
  -id: int
  -researcherId: int
  -workPackageId: int
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

Researcher "1" --> "0..*" Assignment : assigned to
Assignment "1" --> "1" Researcher : researcher
Assignment "1" --> "1" WorkPackage : work package
WorkPackage "1" --> "0..*" Assignment : has team members
WorkPackage "1" --> "1" ResearchGroup : led by
ResearchGroup "1" --> "0..*" WorkPackage : leads
ResearchGroup "1" --> "1" Department : belongs to
Researcher "1" --> "1" ResearchGroup : belongs to
Project "1" --> "0..*" WorkPackage : contains
@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **Researcher**:
  - Belongs to exactly one **ResearchGroup**.
  - Can be assigned to multiple **WorkPackages** via **Assignments**.

- **ResearchGroup**:
  - Belongs to exactly one **Department**.
  - Leads one or more **WorkPackages**.
  - Has zero or more **Researchers** (directly or through assignments).

- **WorkPackage**:
  - Belongs to exactly one **Project**.
  - Is led by exactly one **ResearchGroup**.
  - Has zero or more **Researchers** as team members through **Assignments**.

- **Assignment**:
  - Represents the assignment of a **Researcher** to a **WorkPackage**.
  - Captures the period during which the researcher was assigned.
  - Used to track **service delivery** across groups.

- **Department**:
  - Contains **ResearchGroups**.

---

### Notes:

- When a **Researcher** changes **ResearchGroup**, all current **Assignments** are terminated, and new ones are created to reflect the correct service delivery.
- If **WP leadership** is reassigned, existing **Assignments** may be updated or replaced accordingly to ensure accurate traceability.

